<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Conclusion</strong><br />
TfWM have some great developers and we quickly developed a rapport together. We have built good relations not only at a personal level, but also as organisations.<br />
If the state of our bus stop data in the West Midlands is typical for the UK then we have a lot of work to do to obtain an accurate UK-wide map of bus stops. If we were to  contemplate upgrading throughout the UK I would say it couldn&#8217;t be done without a dedicated full-time team and would consequently need some national sponsorship with a business case for devoting the resources necessary. A region-by-region or city-by-city approach would be more doable. So how about it OSM UK and DfT (Department for Transport)?</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
